"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453863","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-01","<p>The specific information requested is not readily available, and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The information we do have for Employment and Support Allowance claimants by medical condition, including Neoplasms and phase of claim, is published and available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","27706 ; 27707","2016-03-01T16:16:09.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453863/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453863/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453863/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-22","Employment and Support Allowance: Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of people with cancer currently in the work-related activity group of employment and support allowance were previously in the support group.","false","Biography information for Corri Wilson","Ayr, Carrick and Cumnock","Corri Wilson","27708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453864","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-01","<p>Data on Healthcare Professionals’ backgrounds has been recorded for statistical purposes since March 2015. The background of Healthcare Professionals has been recorded as either: Nurse; Physiotherapist; Doctor, or; Occupational Therapist.</p><p>From March 2015 to January 2016, CHDA employed 612 nurses; 66 physiotherapists and 147 doctors on average each month. Occupational therapists have been recruited from July 2015 and the average number employed each month to January 2016 was 10.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-01T17:44:28.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453864/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453864/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453864/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-22","Work Capability Assessment: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) junior doctors, (b) consultants, (c) nurses and (d) healthcare assistants have been employed to undertake work capability assessments in each year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","27691"
