"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453099","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Spending Review underlined the priority this Government attaches to our ambition to build a million homes this Parliament and to double the number of new homeowners. Building on the successful contribution the Homes and Communities Agency made in the last Parliament, the Review will ensure that they are well-placed to deliver the Government’s objectives.</p><p>In line with Cabinet Office guidance, the Review will consider a range of options in looking at how the Agency can operate in the most effective and efficient way.</p><p>We will be seeking evidence from a wide range of sources, including the Agency itself, and will provide an opportunity for interested stakeholders to contribute views. Once this evidence has been collected and conclusions drawn, the Review will report as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","27314 ; 27315 ; 27884","2016-02-29T17:22:20.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453099/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453099/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453099/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Homes and Communities Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the timetable is for the review of the Homes and Communities Agency.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","27316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453100","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-29","<p>To date over £48 million has been paid out to local authorities through the Community and Business Recovery Fund and Council Tax and Business Rates discounts to assist households and businesses affected by the floods caused by Storms Desmond and Eva.</p><p> </p><p>Local authorities have not notified the Department of any allowable costs not covered by the sums transferred. It is expected that further payments will be made shortly as flooded property numbers are confirmed and further funds requested.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","27222 ; 27226 ; 27228 ; 27229 ; 27230","2016-02-29T17:47:19.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453100/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453100/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453100/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Flood Control: Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the cost to the public purse has been of his Department reimbursing local authorities for payments to (a) households and (b) businesses in flood protection grants.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","27227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453101","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-29","<p>The issue of burial space is regularly discussed at meetings of the Burial and Cremation Advisory Group, which is chaired by this department and comprises key stakeholders and representatives within government and the wider burial sector. In addition, the department regularly engages on the issue with individual stakeholders, as appropriate.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-02-29T10:16:51.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453101/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453101/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-19","Cemeteries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what discussions his Department has had with burial authorities and other stakeholders on the reuse of graves.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","27219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453102","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-29","<p>To date over £48 million has been paid out to local authorities through the Community and Business Recovery Fund and Council Tax and Business Rates discounts to assist households and businesses affected by the floods caused by Storms Desmond and Eva.</p><p> </p><p>Local authorities have not notified the Department of any allowable costs not covered by the sums transferred. It is expected that further payments will be made shortly as flooded property numbers are confirmed and further funds requested.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","27222 ; 27226 ; 27227 ; 27229 ; 27230","2016-02-29T17:47:19.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453102/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453102/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453102/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Flood Control: Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, by what date he expects all local authorities to be fully reimbursed for flood protection grants they have paid to (a) households and (b) businesses.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","27228"
