"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453121","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Department for Communities and Local Government does not collect information on the number of people who applied for a Disabled Facilities Grant or the number of successful applicants<strong>. </strong>Information on the number of grants completed and the average cost per grant for the years 2009-10 to 2014-15 is provided in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2009-10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of grants completed</p></td><td><p>44,102</p></td><td><p>45,383</p></td><td><p>43,986</p></td><td><p>36,874</p></td><td><p>42,586</p></td><td><p>33,922</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Average grants awarded</p></td><td><p>£3,356</p></td><td><p>£3,724</p></td><td><p>£4,547</p></td><td><p>£5,966</p></td><td><p>£4,227</p></td><td><p>£5,453</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The above data is provided by local housing authorities in their annual Logasnet returns. LOGASnet is the Department of Communities and Local Government's web-based data capture and payments system. The data is not audited by DCLG.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-02-29T17:27:54.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453121/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453121/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453121/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Disabled Facilities Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, (a) how many people applied for disabled facilities grants, (b) how many such applications were successful and (c) what the average grant award was in each year from 2009-10 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","27552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453122","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-24","<p>The Department expects to complete the review of compliance with the Local Government Transparency Code 2015 by the end of March 2016.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-02-24T16:30:23.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453122/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453122/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453122/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Local Government: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 25 November 2015 to Question 16106, when he expects his Department's review of compliance with the Local Government Transparency Code 2015 to be completed.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","27580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453123","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Property Level Resilience scheme has been designed to enable local approaches to be developed which take account of the fact that many households or businesses may not be able to pay for works up front.</p><p>Local areas are finding local solutions. For example, Northumberland County Council are making Property Level Resilience payments in advance of works being carried out, but following receipt of a survey which highlights the measures required and at least two quotes for high value items.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-02-29T17:28:46.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453123/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453123/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453123/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Flood Control: Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assistance is available to people undertaking flood protection measures who cannot afford to pay for the works before claiming a flood protection grant.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","27553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453124","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-24","<p>As indicated in my earlier answer, the review will be completed by November 2016, the 5<sup>th</sup> anniversary of the Act receiving royal assent</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-02-24T17:29:35.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453124/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453124/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453124/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Local Government: Powers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 5 January 2016 to Question 20554, when he plans to carry out a post-implementation review of the Localism Act 2011.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","27581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453125","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-29","<p>The rate of pay for cleaners working in buildings managed by the Department for Communities and Local Government is between £6.70 and £8.00 per hour depending on seniority, location and duration of tenure. From April 2016, the Department will pay the National Living Wage.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-02-29T17:33:06.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453125/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453125/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453125/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-19","Department for Communities and Local Government: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the rate of pay is for cleaners in his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","27549"
