"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453128","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-24","<p>According to Sport England’s Active Places Power database which maps community sports facilities in England, 15 new athletics tracks have been built in England since 2012. This data can be found at: <a href="http://www.activeplacespower.com/" target="_blank">www.activeplacespower.com</a></p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-02-24T16:25:49.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453128/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453128/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453128/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-19","Athletics: Sportsgrounds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many new athletics tracks have been built since August 2012.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","27359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453129","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-29","<p>According to Sport England’s Active Places Power database which maps community sports facilities in England, 105 new community cricket pitches have been opened in England in the last five years. This data can be found at: www.activeplacespower.com</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-02-29T15:38:45.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453129/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453129/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453129/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-19","Cricket: Sportsgrounds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many new community cricket grounds have been opened in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","27362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453130","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-29","<p /><p> </p><p>The Calder Valley is a beautiful part of the UK and tourism is an essential part of the local economy. We want to ensure that our tourism businesses have as much support as possible as they recover from the recent floods. That is why a new £1m PR campaign was announced by the Prime Minister in Cumbria, on the 28th January, to support businesses ready to receive visitors, and this is part of a wider package of immediate measures to help the area.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-02-29T13:42:18.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453130/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453130/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453130/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-19","Tourism: Calder Valley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to encourage tourism in Calder Valley since the recent flooding and severe weather in that area.","false","Biography information for Craig Whittaker","Calder Valley","Craig Whittaker","27394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453131","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-29","<p>No assessment has been made by DCMS of the direct cost to Calder Valley's tourism industry following the recent flooding. However, some tourism businesses in flood affected areas have reported a drop in bookings of up to 60%. We want to ensure that our tourism businesses have as much support as possible as they recover from the recent floods and that is why a new £1m PR campaign was announced by the Prime Minister in Cumbria, on the 28th January, to support businesses ready to receive visitors, and this is part of a wider package of immediate measures to help the area.</p><p> </p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-02-29T17:05:49.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453131/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453131/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453131/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-19","Tourism: Calder Valley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will estimate the cost to the tourist industry in Calder Valley of recent flooding and severe weather in that area.","false","Biography information for Craig Whittaker","Calder Valley","Craig Whittaker","27395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453132","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>NATO does not have an Ultra Rapid Reaction Corps. I believe the hon. Member is referring to NATO's Very High Readiness Joint Task Force (Land element), which the UK will lead in 2017. When not deployed, its assigned one-star Headquarters, 20 Brigade, will be based in Sennelager, Germany for the duration of this rotational commitment. In response to crisis, the headquarters would move to the most appropriate location.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-29T16:59:08.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453132/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453132/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453132/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","NATO Rapid Reaction Corps: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, where he expects the two-star headquarters of the Ultra Rapid Reaction Corps to be located.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","James Gray","27379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453133","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-25","<p>There are currently seven members of the Defence Cultural Specialist Unit deployed on operations in the Middle East and Afghanistan.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-25T16:07:02.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453133/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453133/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453133/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK armed forces personnel cultural advisers are currently deployed on overseas operations.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","27295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453134","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-25","<p>The Defence Centre for Languages and Culture (DCLC) has delivered specific cultural training to over 621 military students since 2013. This information is not available by year.</p><p>The DCLC has provided cultural training for the Middle East, North Africa and specific courses on Afghan, Kurdish, Gulf States and Moroccan culture; cultural training is also incoporated into all of the DCLC language courses.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-25T16:07:34.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453134/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453134/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453134/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK armed forces personnel have received region-specific culture training at the Defence Centre for Languages and Culture in each year since 2013; and to which regions such training related.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","27296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453135","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-24","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) will be commemorating the Battle of Jutland with a significant and extensive programme of events, not least as the principal delivery partner to the Department of Culture, Media and Sport for the national commemorations in the Orkney Islands and on Jutland Bank on 31 May 2016.</p><p>The Royal Navy will be holding and supporting events throughout the UK and, in addition, will be supporting events in Germany, Sweden, Norway and Denmark.</p><p>The MOD welcomes the opportunity to make such a significant contribution to the commemoration of this historic Naval battle and the wider Great War at Sea.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-02-24T15:30:44.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453135/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453135/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453135/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","Battle of Jutland: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to commemorate the Battle of Jutland.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","27351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453136","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-25","<p>The UK Joint Targeting and Battle Damage Assessment Policy paper, dated 2005 established the baseline principles primarily for coordinating the delivery of lethal effects. This paper has been superseded by Joint Services Policy (JSP) 900 UK Targeting Policy - Edition 2 dated September 2015 which contains the policy and direction on targeting, and guidance on the processes involved and best practice to apply. UK Targeting policy has evolved to incorporate operational lessons identified through Full Spectrum Targeting, apportioning action (lethal and non-lethal) in accordance with desired policy outcomes, and to bring greater interoperability between the UK, NATO and the 5 Eyes Nations (Australia, Canada, New Zealand, the UK, and the US ). JSP 900 cannot yet be placed in the public domain as it would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces and forces cooperating with them. However, we are working to produce a releasable version which is to be published later in 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-25T16:08:08.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453136/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453136/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453136/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place a copy of the UK Joint Targeting and Battle Damage Assessment Policy paper, dated 2005, in the Library.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","27212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453137","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-25","<p>Intake to the UK Regulars by location is unavailable. However, the Ministry of Defence publishes UK Regular strengths by stationed location in our Quarterly Location Statistics: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/location-of-all-uk-regular-service-and-civilian-personnel-quarterly-statistics-index</p><p>Information on intake into the Volunteer Reserve by stationed location is provided in the attached table.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2016-02-25T16:58:44.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453137/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453137/answer","Intake into Future Reserves 2020 Volunteer Reserve by Stationed Location.docx","27213-Intake into the VR Stationed Location","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453137/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","Armed Forces: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people were recruited to the (a) Army, (b) Royal Air Force, (c) Royal Navy and (d) reserve forces in Scotland in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","27213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453138","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>The UK Government has permission to operate from Naval Air Station (NAS) Sigonella. We make frequent use of it, for example in 2015, three Merlin helicopters were based there as a part of Operation WEALD, which provided search and rescue capability in the Mediterranean.</p><p>We are currently operating from NAS Sigonella as part of a NATO anti-submarine warfare exercise, Exercise DYNAMIC MANTA.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-29T17:01:23.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453138/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453138/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453138/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","Italy: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Government has sought from or been given permission by the Italian government for use of the Sigonella air station in Sicily.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","27211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453139","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-24","<p>Between 6 April 2005 and 1 April 2015, 195 war widow(er)s remarried regardless of when they became a war widow(er).</p><p> </p><p>After becoming a war widow prior to 6 April 2005, 135 women remarried between 6 April 2005 and 1 April 2015.</p><p> </p><p>In line with Defence Statistics' Rounding Policy for War Pension Scheme data, figures have been rounded to the nearest five.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","27253","2016-02-24T15:29:52.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453139/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453139/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453139/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","War Widows","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what information his Department holds on the number of war widows who remarried between 6 April 2005 and 1 April 2015.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","27234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453140","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-24","<p>Between 6 April 2005 and 1 April 2015, 195 war widow(er)s remarried regardless of when they became a war widow(er).</p><p> </p><p>After becoming a war widow prior to 6 April 2005, 135 women remarried between 6 April 2005 and 1 April 2015.</p><p> </p><p>In line with Defence Statistics' Rounding Policy for War Pension Scheme data, figures have been rounded to the nearest five.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","27234","2016-02-24T15:29:52.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453140/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453140/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453140/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","War Widows","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what information his Department holds on the number of women who become war widows before 6 April 2005 and remarried between 6 April 2005 and 1 April 2015.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","27253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453141","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>No. The Ministry of Defence received a Host Nation Notification from the US in respect of RAF Lakenheath on 7 January 2015, relating to US F-35 basing.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-29T17:00:51.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453141/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453141/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453141/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","USA: RAF Lakenheath","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 10 February 2016 to Question 25312, whether he has been consulted about proposals for a US drone operation centre at RAF Lakenheath; and whether he has received a Host Nation Notification from the US in respect of RAF Lakenheath in the last year.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","27237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453142","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>The personnel embedded in coalition Headquarters are supporting Operation Shader and wider Middle East security operations.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-02-29T17:01:51.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453142/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453142/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453142/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-19","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to his Written Statement of 17 December 2015, HCWS 431, to which deployed coalitions the UK is party.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","27205"
