"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453197","Department for Education","false","2016-02-25","<p>It is not possible to give an estimate of how much funding the Department has spent on horticultural training, as the post-16 funding formula does not attribute funding to specific subjects. We fund institutions based on their whole programme content and student profile. Institutions then divide their funding between subjects as they see fit.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-02-25T15:29:34.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453197/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453197/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-02-19","Horticulture: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much her Department has spent on horticultural training in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","27421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453198","Department for Education","false","2016-02-24","<p>According to data from EduBase[1], there are eight local authority maintained nurseries in the Burnley constituency, 24 in Lancashire local authority, and 70 in the North West.</p><p>Local authority maintained nurseries are nurseries run by local authorities which are stand-alone and not attached to a primary school. There is therefore more nursery provision in these areas than these figures show; for example, nursery classes in schools and private nurseries.</p><p> </p><p>[1] EduBase as at 9<sup>th</sup> February 2016. Source: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/schools-in-england" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/schools-in-england</a></p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-02-24T16:37:25.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453198/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453198/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453198/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-02-19","Pre-school Education: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many maintained nurseries there are in (a) Burnley, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","27428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453199","Department for Education","false","2016-02-26","<p>The following table provides the full-time equivalent and head count number of workforce staff in service in local authority maintained nursery schools in Burnley parliamentary constituency, Lancashire local authority, North West region and England, November 2014. The figures are from the school workforce census and are the latest available.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Burnley</p></td><td><p>Lancashire</p></td><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>England</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total regular FTE workforce[1]</p></td><td><p>67</p></td><td><p>233</p></td><td><p>774</p></td><td><p>6,142</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total regular head count workforce1</p></td><td><p>82</p></td><td><p>295</p></td><td><p>992</p></td><td><p>8,327</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>[1] Excludes occasional teachers and third party support staff.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-02-26T11:11:44.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453199/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453199/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-02-19","Pre-school Education: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people are employed in maintained nurseries in (a) Burnley, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","27429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453200","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>EDF Energy has contracts with the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (NDA) for the management of AGR fuel. Under these contracts EDF Energy, not the public purse, pays the NDA for the storage of each tonne of AGR fuel that is loaded into the reactor, including for each tonne of fuel loaded during the lifetime extension of the AGR reactors.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:40:42.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453200/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453200/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453200/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453200/answer/previousversion/46985","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Radioactive Waste: Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the additional cost to the public purse will be of storage of additional spent fuel arising from the lifetime extension of nuclear reactors.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453201","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>No. The strategy of the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (NDA) is to complete the THORP reprocessing contracts it has with EDF Energy. In delivering the current strategy the NDA will have created sufficient space to receive and manage all the AGR fuel from EDF Energy’s AGR power stations, which avoids having to build additional storage capacity for AGR fuel.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:41:51.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453201/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453201/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453201/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453201/answer/previousversion/46986","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield: Radioactive Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether new storage facilities will be required at Sellafield to accommodate additional spent fuel arising from the life extension of nuclear reactors.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453202","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>The additional amount of spent fuel arising from the recently announced lifetime extension of 4 AGR stations is anticipated to be in the range of 700-800 tU, based on the current rate of arisings of spent fuel from the AGR fleet.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:42:30.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453202/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453202/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453202/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453202/answer/previousversion/46987","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Radioactive Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what volume of additional spent fuel will be produced as a consequence of the life extension of nuclear reactors.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453203","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>It has not been possible to find copies of any impact assessments related to the moratorium of gas-fired power generation which was introduced by the Government of the time (with a Department of Trade and Industry lead) to allow an analysis of whether the UK energy market was skewed against coal-fired electricity generation.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:13:53.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453203/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453203/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453203/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Gas Fired Power Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will place in the Library copies of the impact assessments produced related to the moratorium on gas fired power stations between 1998 and 2000.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","27405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453204","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister announced a UK/Iceland taskforce to consider the potential for interconnection between the two countries. The taskforce is considering a high-level assessment of the costs and benefits and will make recommendations to Government in May as to whether to continue with a more detailed stage of discussions. This will include an assessment of the impact of the interconnector on system costs.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:21:46.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453204/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453204/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453204/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Electricity Interconnectors: Iceland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what charges the Government plans to levy for connection to the National Grid on the proposed interconnector cable from Iceland.","false","Biography information for Corri Wilson","Ayr, Carrick and Cumnock","Corri Wilson","27325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453205","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-24","<p>The Department already monitors the use of wood for fuel in the UK through two means:</p><ul><li>Analysis of the sustainability data returned to Ofgem (a requirement for generators &gt;50kW under the Renewables Obligation)</li><li>A voluntary questionnaire which asks the large scale biomass electricity users (&gt;50MW) of their plans for sourcing biomass for the next five years.</li></ul><p> </p><p>Volumes of UK wood being used for electricity and CHP generation are expected to remain at a fairly constant level, at around 1.3-1.4million oven dried tonnes per year. There is no indication that use of UK-sourced biomass for electricity is causing resource constraints for other UK wood users (such as the wood products industry).</p><p> </p><p>The conclusions from our most recent analysis1 reinforce what we already understood: that while biomass generation is increasing, the demand for feedstock is being met mostly from imports.</p><p> </p><p><em><strong>[1]</strong></em><em> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/woodfuel-disclosure-survey" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/woodfuel-disclosure-survey</a></em></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-24T13:49:43.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453205/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453205/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453205/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Biofuels: Timber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will undertake an assessment of the effect on the availability of UK-sourced wood supplies of (a) 50MW and under and (b) over 50MW wood-burning biomass plants.","false","Biography information for Susan Elan Jones","Clwyd South","Susan Elan Jones","27354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453206","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-24","<p>The UK Bioenergy Strategy was published by the previous government in 2012 and provides principles that provide a framework to guide policy development for bioenergy. Those principles remain relevant and so a review of the Strategy is not currently considered a priority for the Department.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-24T13:49:25.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453206/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453206/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453206/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Biofuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what plans she has to review the UK Bioenergy Strategy.","false","Biography information for Susan Elan Jones","Clwyd South","Susan Elan Jones","27353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453207","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-03-01","<p>Adaptation is a core component of the Paris Agreement, adopted by the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change in December last year. The Agreement includes a new long-term goal to strengthen adaptation and resilience and reduce vulnerability to climate change. This goal is aligned with the new Global Goals for sustainable development, particularly Goal 13 on climate action. Alongside this, the Paris Agreement includes commitments for each country to take action to adapt according to national circumstances, to share their adaptation planning and to cooperate to help those developing countries who need help to adapt to climate change.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has been and remains committed to leading calls to increase support for adaptation, and we aim to use 50 per cent of our International Climate Fund (ICF) to support adaptation in developing countries. The UK has already taken significant action to support vulnerable countries to adapt to climate change and cope with climate-related events. For example, we have increased our support for climate risk insurance initiatives, such as the Africa Risk Capacity Initiative and the Pacific Catastrophe Risk Assessment and Financing Initiative. We are also funding actions that help build communities’ resilience, including through support for climate services and early warning systems which have an important role to play in helping poor and vulnerable communities be better prepared and more resilient to climate-related risks.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-03-01T15:32:12.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453207/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453207/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453207/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what plans she has to promote a global goal on adaptation to climate change.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","27563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453208","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>The Nuclear Decommissioning Authority has a responsibility to UK tax payers to ensure that Sellafield Ltd has maximum opportunity for improved performance: accelerating hazard reduction and delivering value for money. A new model, part of a suite of changes designed to increase efficiency in the business, is being put in place to help achieve that. The rationale for this model is set out in the Sellafield Model Change (SMC) Outline Business Case.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the change programme are available at <a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/" target="_blank">http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","27456 ; 27457","2016-02-25T15:17:53.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453208/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453208/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453208/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the objectives are of the Sellafield workforce reform initiative; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453209","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>A new model, part of a suite of changes designed to increase efficiency in the business, is being put in place at Sellafield to increase efficiency in the business. The changes will have a positive impact on the Cumbrian economies, through encouraging supply chain companies to locate in the area as part of the Sellafield Change Programme.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the change programme are available at <a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/" target="_blank">http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:15:03.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453209/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453209/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453209/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment her Department has made of the potential effect of the Sellafield workforce reform initiative on workforce salary expenditure by Sellafield Ltd in (a) Copeland, (b) Allerdale, (c) Barrow-in-Furness and (d) Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453210","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>A new model, part of a suite of changes designed to increase efficiency in the business, is being put in place at Sellafield to increase efficiency in the business. The Sellafield Change Programme is deliberately focussed on developing the supply chain for Sellafield to maximise the positive impact on the community.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the change programme are available at <a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/" target="_blank">http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:19:50.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453210/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453210/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453210/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment her Department has made of the potential effect of the Sellafield workforce reform initiative on the economy of (a) Copeland, (b) Allerdale, (c) Barrow-in-Furness and (d) Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453211","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>A new model, part of a suite of changes designed to increase efficiency in the business, is being put in place at Sellafield to deliver savings. There is no additional cost to the public purse from implementing this model change.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the change programme are available at <a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/" target="_blank">http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:19:09.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453211/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453211/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453211/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate her Department has made of the cost to the public purse of the Sellafield workforce reform initiative.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453212","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>DECC Ministers engage regularly with a range of stakeholders, including in relation to the safe, secure and cost-effective decommissioning of the nuclear decommissioning estate.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:21:02.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453212/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453212/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453212/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will meet Sellafield workforce representatives to discuss how better to achieve (a) safer, (b) quicker and (c) more efficient decommissioning of the Sellafield site.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453213","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>Since July 1998, 35 gas fired power stations (i.e. electricity generating installations with a capacity of 50 MW+) have opened in the UK.</p><p> </p><p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/446457/dukes5_10.xls" target="_blank">Digest of United Kingdom Energy Statistics (DUKES), Table 5.10</a></em></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-02-25T15:12:42.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453213/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453213/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453213/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Gas Fired Power Stations: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many gas fired power stations have been built in the UK since July 1998.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","27447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453214","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>The Nuclear Decommissioning Authority has a responsibility to UK tax payers to ensure that Sellafield Ltd has maximum opportunity for improved performance: accelerating hazard reduction and delivering value for money. A new model, part of a suite of changes designed to increase efficiency in the business, is being put in place to help achieve that. The rationale for this model is set out in the Sellafield Model Change (SMC) Outline Business Case.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the change programme are available at <a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/" target="_blank">http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","27457 ; 27461","2016-02-25T15:17:52.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453214/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453214/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453214/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment her Department has made of how the Sellafield workforce reform initiative will ensure (a) safer, (b) quicker and (c) more efficient delivery of decommissioning at Sellafield.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453215","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-25","<p>The Nuclear Decommissioning Authority has a responsibility to UK tax payers to ensure that Sellafield Ltd has maximum opportunity for improved performance: accelerating hazard reduction and delivering value for money. A new model, part of a suite of changes designed to increase efficiency in the business, is being put in place to help achieve that. The rationale for this model is set out in the Sellafield Model Change (SMC) Outline Business Case.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the change programme are available at <a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/" target="_blank">http://www.nda.gov.uk/contracts-and-competition/sellafield-model-change-programme/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","27456 ; 27461","2016-02-25T15:17:52.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453215/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453215/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453215/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-19","Sellafield: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether her Department has made an assessment of the potential savings to the public purse arising from the Sellafield workforce reform initiative.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","27457"
